00:41.503 --> 00:43.514
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

00:44.138 --> 00:46.182
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:50.204 --> 00:52.248
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

01:00.837 --> 01:02.880
[CRASHING]

01:07.470 --> 01:09.515
[PANTING]

01:45.503 --> 01:47.548
[CAR APPROACHING]

01:47.637 --> 01:50.114
Hey! Hey!

01:54.204 --> 01:55.881
Jesus!

01:56.703 --> 01:58.714
[CAR HONKS]

01:59.103 --> 02:00.824
What the hell?

02:07.988 --> 02:09.548
Hey!

02:10.238 --> 02:11.781
Hello?

02:12.737 --> 02:14.557
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

02:14.637 --> 02:16.514
Are you all right in there?

02:18.903 --> 02:20.714
Hey, can you hear me?

02:21.437 --> 02:23.014
Jesus.

02:26.503 --> 02:28.174
Holy shit.

02:39.004 --> 02:41.082
[PHONE RINGING]

02:43.737 --> 02:46.557
- OPERATOR: <i>911, what is your emergency?</i>
- I need help. There's a girl here.

02:46.637 --> 02:51.791
She's in some kind of an accident
or something. I think she's dead.

02:51.871 --> 02:54.423
OPERATOR: <i>All right, sir, calm down.
Where are you right now?</i>

02:54.503 --> 02:57.490
I just passed a sign
that said Woodmore County.

02:57.570 --> 02:59.463
<i>I'm sorry, you're breaking up.
Can you repeat that again?</i>

02:59.543 --> 03:03.991
Ah, shit. It's Woodmore. I don't know
what the name of the road is.

03:04.071 --> 03:06.124
<i>Sir, calm down. Can I have your name please?</i>

03:06.204 --> 03:08.081
Yeah, it's...

03:10.503 --> 03:12.081
<i>Sir?</i>

03:21.071 --> 03:22.581
Liam.

03:24.370 --> 03:26.447
[CROW CAWING]

03:59.430 --> 04:01.394
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

04:11.337 --> 04:13.059
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

04:20.988 --> 04:22.831
Jesus Christ.

04:23.287 --> 04:25.164
[CRASHING]

04:25.370 --> 04:27.414
[HONKING]

06:06.487 --> 06:08.064
Hello?

07:10.103 --> 07:12.090
[VOICE MAIL PLAYING]
<i>Hi there. You've reached Liam Hartwell.</i>

07:12.170 --> 07:15.209
<i>If you're calling concerning a landscaping
job, please reach me on my cell...</i>

07:15.289 --> 07:17.858
<i>...at 555-0968.</i>

07:17.938 --> 07:19.991
- <i>Leave a message at the beep.</i>
- [BEEP]

07:20.070 --> 07:23.681
COMPUTER VOICE: <i>If you would like to
change your welcome message, press 1.</i>

07:27.489 --> 07:29.157
[EXHALES] Christ.

07:29.237 --> 07:31.313
[SIGHS]

07:32.042 --> 07:33.454
Fuck.

07:51.203 --> 07:53.214
[PANTING]

08:04.871 --> 08:06.157
[TV PLAYING]

08:06.237 --> 08:08.457
MAN: <i>Are you ruling out
the possibility of biological warfare?</i>

08:08.537 --> 08:11.675
SHERIFF: <i>Like I said before,
until proper autopsies...</i>

08:11.755 --> 08:13.825
- <i>...can be performed, we...</i>
- [REPORTERS CLAMORING]

08:15.103 --> 08:18.172
- MAN: <i>Is the air safe to breathe?</i>
- <i>We have to wait for the coroner's report...</i>

08:18.252 --> 08:21.357
<i>...before we can stipulate what it is
that actually happened here.</i>

08:21.437 --> 08:24.190
<i>Now, whether the air
is safe to breathe or not...</i>

08:24.270 --> 08:26.558
- <i>...I can't say at this time.</i>
- [REPORTERS CLAMORING]

08:32.370 --> 08:34.380
[CAR APPROACHING]

08:43.736 --> 08:45.289
- [KNOCKING AT DOOR]
- Hey!

08:46.237 --> 08:48.013
Hey! Get out of here!

08:49.036 --> 08:52.113
No! Go! Get out of here! It's not safe!

08:53.170 --> 08:55.964
You can't stay outside. Go!

08:58.969 --> 09:00.740
Stupid.

09:26.903 --> 09:28.714
Go home!

09:32.537 --> 09:34.314
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

09:50.753 --> 09:51.690
[CROW CAWING]

09:51.770 --> 09:55.357
WOMAN ON TV: <i>I spoke with him earlier
and he confirms that the signs of death...</i>

09:55.437 --> 09:57.357
- <i>...were similar to Melanie Walker's...</i>
- [CROW CAWING]

09:57.437 --> 10:00.457
<i>...the 29-year-old woman
who was found earlier this morning.</i>

10:00.537 --> 10:03.957
<i>I also had an opportunity to talk
with Sheriff Laredo earlier on...</i>

10:04.037 --> 10:07.590
<i>...concerning the current state of
affairs. This is what he had to say.</i>

10:07.670 --> 10:10.823
SHERIFF: <i>We've established
only two occurrences so far.</i>

10:10.902 --> 10:13.989
<i>One alongside route 131
going into Woodmore...</i>

10:14.069 --> 10:17.490
<i>...and the other at Sophie's Diner,
just a few miles away.</i>

10:17.570 --> 10:22.890
<i>So the good news for now is that
these incidents seem to be localized.</i>

10:22.970 --> 10:27.623
WOMAN: <i>Now residents in and around this area
are considerably nervous about all this.</i>

10:28.302 --> 10:30.791
- Hey! Shut the hell up!
- [CROW CONTINUES CAWING]

10:31.551 --> 10:35.357
<i>...a gripping interview with the person
who first made this recent discovery...</i>

10:35.437 --> 10:40.390
<i>...Sophie's Diner busboy, Dylan Keen,
who came in this morning late...</i>

10:40.470 --> 10:42.714
<i>...which might have actually saved his life.</i>

10:54.703 --> 10:56.746
[CROW CAWING]

12:43.803 --> 12:45.747
Oh, shit!

12:47.470 --> 12:49.514
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

13:00.736 --> 13:02.813
[PANTING]

14:12.503 --> 14:15.140
MAN ON RADIO:
<i>The Woodmore string of mysterious deaths.</i>

14:15.220 --> 14:18.241
<i>The latter also confirmed that the
coroner's office has officially ruled out...</i>

14:18.321 --> 14:20.357
<i>...the possibility of an airborne virus...</i>

14:20.437 --> 14:23.450
<i>...but is still uncertain as to
what is causing these deaths...</i>

14:23.530 --> 14:27.523
<i>...and that the possibility of a contagion
has not yet been dismissed.</i>

14:27.602 --> 14:31.037
<i>In related news, many local residents
have been voicing concerns...</i>

14:31.117 --> 14:35.348
<i>...about these deaths being possibly
related to some form of terrorist activity.</i>

14:36.669 --> 14:38.712
[GROANS]

14:41.137 --> 14:43.180
[CAR APPROACHING]

14:56.170 --> 14:58.023
Oh, fuck.

14:58.602 --> 15:00.613
FEMALE COP:
We've got a window pane back here.

15:05.069 --> 15:06.947
The door's unlocked.

15:08.702 --> 15:10.923
Mr. Hartwell, are you in there?

15:11.003 --> 15:13.933
It's Woodmore Police. We found your truck.

15:16.237 --> 15:19.357
- We are coming in.
- MALE COP: All right, I'll go inside.

15:19.437 --> 15:21.680
- You check the surroundings.
- Gotcha.

15:35.970 --> 15:37.514
Fuck.

15:47.343 --> 15:49.117
I'm gonna take a look at the shed.

15:56.902 --> 15:58.913
[EXHALES]

16:08.313 --> 16:10.622
Uh, Tim, we've got a situation over here.

16:10.702 --> 16:14.756
Dead birds, white eyes, like the shit
at Sophie's Diner type of thing.

16:14.836 --> 16:17.713
TIM: <i>All right, screw this.
I'll meet you back at the car</i>.

16:23.702 --> 16:25.712
[ENGINE STARTS]

16:27.037 --> 16:29.047
Fuck. Fuck.

17:11.839 --> 17:13.357
[CLATTERING]

17:13.435 --> 17:16.114
- Oh, shit.
- WOMAN: Hello?

17:18.237 --> 17:20.113
Is anybody in there?

17:20.969 --> 17:22.857
- Stop!
- Who's in there?

17:22.936 --> 17:25.730
- You've gotta get away from here!
- I just wanna talk to you.

17:25.810 --> 17:28.248
No, don't come any closer. Please!

17:30.170 --> 17:32.047
Is your name Liam?

17:32.836 --> 17:34.680
Are you Liam Hartwell?

17:36.536 --> 17:41.023
Look, we can talk, but just...
look, just get away from the shed.

17:41.602 --> 17:43.422
- Why?
- Goddammit, just do what I say.

17:43.502 --> 17:45.947
You need to get away from me. Now!

17:46.969 --> 17:48.480
Please!

17:50.702 --> 17:52.780
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

17:53.669 --> 17:55.513
I just wanna talk to you.

18:23.936 --> 18:25.446
Liam?

18:26.636 --> 18:28.180
Yeah?

18:29.170 --> 18:30.693
Do you know who I am?

18:32.702 --> 18:35.323
No. Who are you?

18:35.402 --> 18:38.223
I was in your truck. We had an accident.

18:38.303 --> 18:40.379
You were in the truck with me?

18:40.949 --> 18:43.060
I didn't see you when I woke up.

18:45.002 --> 18:47.090
Look, I'm sorry, but...

18:47.669 --> 18:50.713
...you're gonna have to help me out here,
'cause I don't remember any of it.

18:51.203 --> 18:54.125
The truck, the crash, you.

18:54.502 --> 18:56.047
Nothing.

18:57.170 --> 18:59.180
I don't believe this.

18:59.287 --> 19:00.617
What?

19:04.137 --> 19:06.213
I don't know who I am.

19:07.366 --> 19:09.613
And I don't remember anything either.

19:10.602 --> 19:12.386
Wait, what do you mean?

19:12.469 --> 19:14.622
Jesus Christ.

19:14.702 --> 19:18.580
Wait, wait, wait. Hold on.
What... how is that even possible?

19:21.769 --> 19:24.980
Look, can we go inside?
I wanna take a look around.

19:29.806 --> 19:31.346
Hey.

19:32.003 --> 19:33.813
What's the matter?

19:37.636 --> 19:41.513
Look, uh... what don't you
just go inside and I'll...

19:52.336 --> 19:54.180
Is everything okay?

19:58.087 --> 19:59.664
Yeah.

20:00.433 --> 20:01.903
Yeah, it is.

20:23.170 --> 20:25.180
How did you know to come here?

20:26.536 --> 20:30.822
A cop told me the truck was
registered to a Liam Hartwell.

20:30.902 --> 20:33.147
So here I am.

20:34.170 --> 20:35.834
I didn't have anything on me.

20:36.752 --> 20:39.963
So I just figured you were my best shot.

20:42.336 --> 20:45.988
I mean, it was either that or stay
at the homeless shelter and let some...

20:46.700 --> 20:48.947
...social worker figure it out.

20:59.469 --> 21:01.312
WOMAN: Was that you?

21:08.669 --> 21:12.102
Look, I don't think you live here. I mean...

21:12.881 --> 21:15.746
...I didn't find any women's
clothes or anything.

21:21.769 --> 21:23.647
What's with all the tape?

21:24.736 --> 21:27.147
They said there was a virus or something.

21:27.569 --> 21:30.657
- That's what they thought anyway.
- Yeah, I heard about that.

21:31.236 --> 21:33.522
I mean, you know it's over, though, right?

21:33.602 --> 21:36.412
They're saying it's not
in the air or anything.

21:43.402 --> 21:45.694
I don't suppose you know your password.

21:47.002 --> 21:49.027
Your guess is as good as mine.

22:15.302 --> 22:17.393
[SNIFFING]

22:30.269 --> 22:34.298
WOMAN: Hey, if you thought it wasn't safe
outside, then why were you out there?

22:46.569 --> 22:48.329
Are you okay?

22:51.752 --> 22:56.176
Do you know some place
called Smithburg or Oakdale?

22:58.469 --> 23:01.322
Here. County line.

23:01.652 --> 23:03.639
It's right next to a bridge.

23:03.719 --> 23:05.610
And we were both there.

23:21.252 --> 23:23.109
What is it?

23:23.669 --> 23:26.160
Nothing. Let's get out of here.

23:44.802 --> 23:47.027
Sorry. I'm sorry.

23:48.569 --> 23:50.994
I'm just trying to figure us out, that's all.

23:58.336 --> 24:00.226
So, what do I call you?

24:01.169 --> 24:03.657
Everybody's been calling me Jane Doe.

24:06.236 --> 24:09.494
I guess it's something I've gotten used to.

24:12.686 --> 24:14.209
Jane.

24:15.502 --> 24:17.359
All right, then.

24:51.052 --> 24:53.109
I don't remember this place at all.

24:55.602 --> 24:57.493
We were here.

24:59.036 --> 25:00.694
Dammit.

25:09.036 --> 25:12.427
You know, when you asked me
before if I knew you?

25:13.069 --> 25:15.360
I didn't. I still don't.

25:19.102 --> 25:21.560
- Just...
- What?

25:22.872 --> 25:24.911
I just have this feeling like...

25:27.152 --> 25:28.877
...I feel like I know you.

25:33.068 --> 25:34.626
Yeah?

25:39.302 --> 25:41.790
When I was at the hospital, I had this dream.

25:42.669 --> 25:45.760
I mean, I'm not even sure
if this is a real memory or not.

25:46.869 --> 25:49.246
But in the dream, I'm...

25:49.326 --> 25:52.994
...I'm a kid, I'm like seven or eight...

25:54.169 --> 25:58.089
...and I'm at the mall with my family.

25:58.169 --> 26:00.194
Faces I can't even make out.

26:02.001 --> 26:05.093
We're all just waiting
in line to see Santa Claus.

26:06.302 --> 26:09.290
And there's this kid who's up
on Santa's lap and...

26:10.147 --> 26:11.959
...he reaches up...

26:12.869 --> 26:15.757
...and he pulls the guy's beard down.

26:16.336 --> 26:18.394
And I see this and I just...

26:19.629 --> 26:21.460
...I just lose it.

26:22.901 --> 26:26.103
I just ran, I just ran all the way up
into the parking lot.

26:29.269 --> 26:31.160
I guess I couldn't take it.

26:34.102 --> 26:36.926
It's the only thing I remember
from my whole life.

26:39.069 --> 26:40.926
Pretty useless, huh?

26:41.868 --> 26:45.089
No. I disagree.

26:45.169 --> 26:47.857
If anything, it proves
that everything is still in there.

26:47.936 --> 26:49.827
It's not lost.

26:50.669 --> 26:53.326
You just have to find
a better way to get at it.

27:02.736 --> 27:04.253
It's too late for that.

27:05.102 --> 27:06.956
You can't stay here.

27:07.036 --> 27:08.560
<i>Jane?</i>

27:09.669 --> 27:12.565
I'm fine, I just... I just
remembered something. I...

27:12.645 --> 27:15.921
...I threw something into the water.
It was like, um...

27:16.001 --> 27:18.434
...it was papers, or...

27:19.215 --> 27:22.824
- ...I feel like it's...
- Hey, take your time.

27:23.702 --> 27:25.371
You were there.

27:26.602 --> 27:29.826
I feel like I was leaving something behind.

27:31.036 --> 27:33.256
God, this is so frustrating.

27:33.985 --> 27:36.843
- Why were we here?
- I don't know.

27:40.719 --> 27:44.887
Look. The cops didn't find anything
in that pickup truck, right?

27:46.669 --> 27:48.867
What about the crash site itself?

27:55.336 --> 27:59.289
ON RADIO: <i>In a press briefing held earlier
today by the State Medical Examiner's Office.</i>

27:59.369 --> 28:02.906
<i>We are currently referring to these deaths
as attacks on the human body...</i>

28:02.986 --> 28:05.422
<i>...carried out by forces outside of nature...</i>

28:05.502 --> 28:09.356
<i>...meaning that whatever the cause,
they are, in all likelihood, man-made.</i>

28:09.436 --> 28:12.522
<i>In light of this new information,
Woodmore law enforcement has announced...</i>

28:12.602 --> 28:15.859
<i>...they will now be cooperating
with state officials...</i>

28:28.636 --> 28:30.789
Did the cops manage
to figure out why we crashed?

28:30.869 --> 28:34.855
They didn't say. And I heard there was
another car that went off the road?

28:34.935 --> 28:37.656
One of those people that died from
the virus or whatever they're calling it.

28:37.736 --> 28:40.799
But I don't think that
had anything to do with us.

28:43.402 --> 28:45.463
Let's go down and have a look.

29:02.236 --> 29:05.271
What the hell happened here?

29:27.536 --> 29:29.611
I don't think a fire did this.

29:39.701 --> 29:41.793
[THUNDERCLAP]

29:43.369 --> 29:45.119
[GASPS]

29:45.199 --> 29:46.257
What is it?

29:49.069 --> 29:51.156
- Where were you?
- What?

29:51.236 --> 29:53.393
When you woke up, where were you?

29:53.801 --> 29:56.339
I... I was over here. I mean...

29:57.336 --> 29:58.701
...here.

29:58.781 --> 30:03.220
I think I was over here.
I mean, it was so goddamn dark, but...

30:04.536 --> 30:06.959
Yeah, I think it was somewhere around here.

30:08.302 --> 30:09.759
Why?

30:14.019 --> 30:15.577
Liam?

30:17.236 --> 30:19.126
Look, we've gotta talk.

30:20.436 --> 30:23.526
When I got out of here,
something was going on with me.

30:24.768 --> 30:26.889
I didn't know about it at first.

30:27.768 --> 30:29.721
I mean, I...

30:29.801 --> 30:32.721
...I thought it was in the air,
or I don't know, a virus or something.

30:32.801 --> 30:35.622
I mean, the birds were falling
out of the goddamn sky, for fuck's sakes.

30:35.701 --> 30:37.726
What are you talking about?

30:39.768 --> 30:41.590
All right, uh...

30:42.569 --> 30:46.322
...the girl, the one in the car,
the one that died.

30:46.402 --> 30:48.049
Yeah.

30:48.768 --> 30:50.988
That was me.

30:51.068 --> 30:52.989
- What?
- I didn't know about it. I...

30:53.069 --> 30:55.778
...I mean, I didn't do it on purpose.
I didn't even know why I was doing it.

30:55.858 --> 30:57.859
Doing what?

30:58.154 --> 30:59.688
Killing them.

30:59.768 --> 31:03.721
It was like I was just sucking the life
right out of them just by coming close.

31:03.801 --> 31:07.322
Look, I know it sounds insane,
but it happened, all right?

31:07.402 --> 31:10.494
It happened. I mean, people
would just walk up to me and...

31:12.102 --> 31:15.522
...they'd just drop, they'd fucking drop.

31:15.601 --> 31:19.222
Jane, that's why you found me
hiding out all the way back to my shed.

31:19.302 --> 31:21.322
I was just trying
to keep away from everybody.

31:21.402 --> 31:23.821
- This is crazy.
- Jane, listen to me!

31:23.901 --> 31:26.581
That was me. I killed those people.

31:29.086 --> 31:32.656
But, look... look, whatever it was,
whatever I had inside of me is gone now.

31:32.736 --> 31:36.593
- How can you be sure about that?
- No, please trust me. I know I'm fine.

31:37.801 --> 31:39.626
Why are you telling me this now?

31:41.469 --> 31:43.693
Because look at where you're standing.

31:45.336 --> 31:48.056
Whatever happened here,
it happened to both of us.

31:48.136 --> 31:50.855
Yeah, I know that. I said
that I was standing here, but...

31:50.935 --> 31:54.222
...it was so goddamn dark, I could've been
all the way over there for all I know.

31:54.302 --> 31:57.159
So you didn't notice
anything different about yourself?

31:57.801 --> 31:59.522
- No.
- I mean, nothing even...

31:59.601 --> 32:02.655
...I mean, remotely weird happen to you
since you crawled out of this place?

32:02.735 --> 32:05.042
No, and I certainly didn't kill anybody.

32:05.402 --> 32:06.820
LIAM: Jane, wait!

32:10.835 --> 32:13.788
Jane! Jane, stop! Goddammit, I'm sorry!

32:13.868 --> 32:15.555
Oh, you're sorry?

32:15.635 --> 32:18.821
How do I even know it's safe
to be around you right now?

32:18.901 --> 32:21.371
- What if that thing comes back on?
- It won't.

32:21.451 --> 32:24.156
And what if it does?
And what if you end up killing me?

32:24.236 --> 32:26.206
Have you thought about that?

32:26.286 --> 32:28.256
JANE: You should have told me before, Liam.

32:28.336 --> 32:30.393
Hold on a minute, honey, okay?

32:31.658 --> 32:35.949
- Hey there, you guys all right?
- Yeah, we're fine, just leave us alone.

32:36.029 --> 32:39.676
- Ma'am, are you all right?
- I can't do this.

32:40.625 --> 32:42.256
- Jane!
- WOMAN: Sir?

32:42.336 --> 32:44.193
What do you want?

32:47.369 --> 32:51.568
- Look, we're just...
- Hold on there. Are you Liam Hartwell?

32:52.169 --> 32:53.726
Yeah.

32:55.002 --> 32:56.755
We've been looking for you.

32:56.835 --> 32:59.386
On account of your truck
has been found right down...

33:04.019 --> 33:05.521
JANE: Liam?

33:05.901 --> 33:07.798
What's going on?

33:15.469 --> 33:19.447
- Oh, my God!
- No, no, no! Jane! Jane, wait! Jane!

33:21.102 --> 33:23.555
Jane! Stop! Just stop! Stop!

33:23.635 --> 33:26.535
- Let me go! Don't touch me.
- Just stop!

33:26.615 --> 33:29.189
Look, you're not gonna die.

33:29.269 --> 33:31.759
Okay? I promise you. You're not gonna die.

33:33.386 --> 33:35.156
What the hell just happened?

33:38.768 --> 33:41.826
We've gotta get the hell out of here. Please!

33:44.202 --> 33:45.759
Please.

33:46.768 --> 33:48.625
Trust me.

33:51.202 --> 33:52.330
GIRL ON PHONE: <i>Mom?</i>

33:52.922 --> 33:56.173
<i>Mom, are you there? Mom?</i>

34:01.269 --> 34:03.159
JANE: What are we doing here?

34:03.635 --> 34:05.525
Walk that way.

34:06.136 --> 34:09.561
- What?
- Jane, just walk that way.

34:09.641 --> 34:11.201
Please.

34:13.967 --> 34:15.993
[GOAT BLEATING]

34:18.501 --> 34:20.179
Stop!

34:21.369 --> 34:24.993
- If you don't tell me what we're doing...
- Now back away.

34:32.735 --> 34:34.360
Jesus.

34:38.801 --> 34:41.929
- What the hell just happened?
- You moved.

34:43.335 --> 34:46.821
- Are you saying I did this?
- No, I did.

34:46.900 --> 34:50.193
I've been doing it all along
and you've been stopping it...

34:51.186 --> 34:53.076
...without even knowing.

34:55.400 --> 34:57.243
Oh, my God.

34:57.668 --> 35:00.989
- We've gotta get to a hospital.
- What, are you crazy?

35:01.868 --> 35:04.156
There's gotta be some tests they can do.

35:04.236 --> 35:07.056
Blood analysis, some kind
of brain scan, something.

35:07.136 --> 35:09.189
I've been to the hospital.

35:09.269 --> 35:12.588
They scanned me because of the accident
and nothing weird popped up.

35:12.668 --> 35:15.755
Well, you weren't the one killing people,
were you? We have to do this.

35:15.835 --> 35:18.621
You wanna what? You wanna walk
into a hospital and tell them what?

35:18.701 --> 35:21.056
- Jane... we need to do this.
- That you're radiating death?

35:21.136 --> 35:23.916
You saw how I reacted when you told me.
Why don't you just imagine that...

35:23.996 --> 35:26.059
...on a much larger scale?

35:29.885 --> 35:32.159
We have to be smart about this.

35:38.635 --> 35:41.122
If we go to a hospital a couple
of counties down from here...

35:41.202 --> 35:44.286
...somewhere where the police
aren't actually looking for me.

35:44.365 --> 35:48.855
Look, I know it sounds risky, but I need
to figure out what this thing is.

35:48.935 --> 35:53.988
Once we do that, hopefully,
we can make the police understand.

35:57.418 --> 36:01.922
Look, we can tell a doctor that you've
been having trouble remembering...

36:02.002 --> 36:03.821
...because of the accident.

36:03.901 --> 36:05.926
I mean, that much is true.

36:06.501 --> 36:08.622
They'll give you a CT scan.

36:09.301 --> 36:11.359
That's at least what they did for me.

36:33.618 --> 36:36.256
I'm sorry. I should've told you.

36:36.735 --> 36:38.793
We're in this together now.

36:43.701 --> 36:46.089
How many days ago was this accident?

36:46.169 --> 36:48.056
Three nights ago.

36:48.685 --> 36:51.375
You really should have come
to the hospital right away.

37:04.871 --> 37:06.621
[GASPS]

37:06.701 --> 37:08.755
Mr. Hartwell? Is everything okay?

37:08.835 --> 37:10.936
Yes, sorry. [CLEARS THROAT]

37:11.635 --> 37:14.488
DOCTOR: Right, let's get you up
to that scan right away.

37:14.568 --> 37:16.392
Come with me.

37:21.635 --> 37:24.089
Okay, everything's all set to go.

37:24.169 --> 37:26.789
So, ma'am, if you could just step outside.

37:27.768 --> 37:32.155
- No, no, she's gotta stay in here with me.
- The scan is only gonna take a few minutes.

37:32.234 --> 37:35.655
- I can't be in here alone.
- Yeah, he gets claustrophobic sometimes.

37:35.735 --> 37:38.355
Okay, well, we have some medication
we can give you for that.

37:38.435 --> 37:41.989
- No, you don't understand. Please.
- You can't have anybody else in the room.

37:42.069 --> 37:46.358
Can I just go in the booth with you? I mean,
at the very least, he'll be able to see me.

37:48.268 --> 37:49.826
Please.

37:55.901 --> 37:59.588
WOMAN: <i>Okay, we're all set to go here,
so just remember to stay still...</i>

37:59.668 --> 38:01.893
...and we will be done in no time at all.

38:03.735 --> 38:05.588
<i>All right, here we go.</i>

38:05.668 --> 38:07.493
[MACHINE HUMMING]

38:28.768 --> 38:31.289
So you didn't see anything
weird on that monitor?

38:32.168 --> 38:34.821
I don't know, I mean,
I wouldn't even know what to look for.

38:34.901 --> 38:36.755
What about the girl, how did she react?

38:36.835 --> 38:38.721
Did it seem like
she might have seen anything?

38:38.801 --> 38:40.626
I don't think so.

38:43.036 --> 38:45.237
What's taking them so goddamn long?

38:51.102 --> 38:55.022
WOMAN ON TV: <i>A new lead today in the
mysterious death of a Woodmore County officer.</i>

38:55.102 --> 38:59.288
<i>The officer's son confirms hearing his mother
speak the name Liam Hartwell...</i>

38:59.368 --> 39:01.321
<i>...only moments before her death...</i>

39:01.401 --> 39:04.769
<i>...which led police to Hartwell's home
where they made a shocking discovery...</i>

39:04.849 --> 39:09.104
<i>...just behind me here in a field opposite
the home. One more dead body...</i>

39:09.183 --> 39:12.721
<i>...showing signs of death identical
to those found earlier this week.</i>

39:12.801 --> 39:16.455
<i>State law enforcement has officially
declared Hartwell armed and dangerous.</i>

39:16.535 --> 39:20.776
- <i>And they are asking anyone that...</i>
- Shit! We have to get out of here.

39:24.368 --> 39:27.585
- Fuck!
- Wait, wait, no.

39:27.665 --> 39:31.388
Maybe we can just explain it to them. We're
here, aren't we? We were getting tests done.

39:31.468 --> 39:33.621
Tests? Liam, you killed one of their own.

39:33.701 --> 39:37.221
These people don't wanna talk to you.
They wanna bring you in.

39:37.301 --> 39:40.822
Liam, they will separate us.

39:41.201 --> 39:45.225
Mr. Hartwell? I was just on my way
to see you. Is everything all right?

39:45.835 --> 39:47.555
LIAM: What does it say?

39:47.635 --> 39:50.539
- Pardon?
- The scan, what did it say?

39:51.468 --> 39:54.181
- DOCTOR: We're not doing this here.
- We don't have time for this.

39:54.261 --> 39:57.521
You can either come with me to consultation
or you can just schedule another appointment.

39:57.701 --> 39:59.455
- What the hell?
- Tell me what the scan says.

39:59.535 --> 40:00.995
- Liam, they're coming.
- Tell me.

40:01.074 --> 40:02.621
Nothing.

40:03.300 --> 40:05.925
What do you mean nothing?
You must have read it wrong.

40:06.335 --> 40:07.472
- Let's go.
- You're fine.

40:07.552 --> 40:09.999
- There's nothing the matter with you.
- Liam, come on.

40:11.901 --> 40:14.125
WOMAN: Hey! Hey! Police!

40:16.902 --> 40:19.158
Okay, you take that one, I'll go this way.

40:25.201 --> 40:27.058
JANE: I think we lost them.

40:27.268 --> 40:29.069
The elevator, it's over here.

40:50.901 --> 40:52.355
Jane!

40:52.835 --> 40:55.371
- Jane!
- Liam!

40:55.451 --> 40:57.926
- Jane! No!
- Liam!

41:01.635 --> 41:03.246
MAN: Are you okay, buddy?

41:06.688 --> 41:09.268
Everybody just get out of here,
okay? All of you.

41:09.348 --> 41:11.593
- What's the matter?
- All of you! Get out!

41:13.000 --> 41:16.515
When those doors open, run.
Do you understand me?

41:16.595 --> 41:19.115
Run! Get out of here!

41:19.195 --> 41:22.526
No! Go! Go! Get out! Go! Move!

41:30.735 --> 41:32.826
No! Shit!

41:39.668 --> 41:41.092
Fuck.

41:46.736 --> 41:48.926
What? Fuck!

42:05.801 --> 42:07.647
Come on, come on, come on.

42:10.735 --> 42:12.292
No.

42:15.191 --> 42:16.873
Come on!

42:17.201 --> 42:19.258
Come on. Come on.

42:21.698 --> 42:23.258
Liam!

42:23.801 --> 42:26.688
- Oh, my God! Are you all right?
- I'm fine. Everybody's fine.

42:26.768 --> 42:30.155
- I'm sorry. I shouldn't have stopped.
- Let's get out of here.

42:30.235 --> 42:32.435
Hey. Hey, stop.

42:32.515 --> 42:34.558
No, this way, come on.

42:41.068 --> 42:42.925
LIAM: Come on.

43:27.635 --> 43:29.525
This place looks good.

43:31.950 --> 43:33.843
Are you all right?

43:35.068 --> 43:36.925
I was missing.

43:38.934 --> 43:40.826
I still am.

43:42.735 --> 43:45.992
What I've learned about
my life so far, it just doesn't...

43:47.201 --> 43:49.062
...it doesn't seem right.

43:52.101 --> 43:54.726
I have this feeling like I shouldn't go back.

43:56.535 --> 43:58.577
Look, we're both pretty tired.

43:59.301 --> 44:02.005
I think the best thing we can do is to...

44:02.085 --> 44:05.759
...get some rest and then look at this
thing with fresh eyes tomorrow, alright?

45:59.868 --> 46:03.088
WOMAN ON RADIO: <i>All across
the board, sunny skies and clear...</i>

46:03.168 --> 46:05.226
[MAN SPEAKING OVER RADIO]

46:07.035 --> 46:08.855
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER RADIO]

46:08.935 --> 46:10.988
REPORTER:
<i>...in relation to the Woodmore incidents.</i>

46:11.068 --> 46:14.272
<i>Smithburg County police chief also revealed
that Hartwell was accompanied...</i>

46:14.352 --> 46:17.388
<i>...by a local woman
by the name of Rose Daerwood.</i>

46:17.468 --> 46:19.988
<i>The woman had immediately
been identified by her husband...</i>

46:20.068 --> 46:24.444
<i>...local store owner, Sam Daerwood after the
latter had seen security camera footage...</i>

46:24.524 --> 46:27.754
<i>...broadcast on Channel 4 News earlier today.</i>

46:27.834 --> 46:31.488
<i>Daerwood, who was also present at
the press conference, had this to say.</i>

46:31.568 --> 46:33.920
SAM: <i>I don't care what
you've gotten yourself into.</i>

46:34.000 --> 46:36.288
<i>Whatever it is, we can work it out.</i>

46:36.368 --> 46:40.421
<i>Please, Rose, just come home. I love you.</i>

46:40.501 --> 46:43.225
REPORTER: <i>Police are asking for anyone
with information on the whereabouts...</i>

46:43.305 --> 46:47.521
<i>...of both Rose Daerwood and Liam Hartwell
to contact their local authorities...</i>

46:47.601 --> 46:50.720
<i>...and warn that Hartwell is still
considered armed and dangerous.</i>

47:00.201 --> 47:02.092
LIAM: So, what do you wanna do?

47:03.635 --> 47:05.155
Maybe...

47:05.535 --> 47:07.854
...maybe it's worth a shot meeting him.
I mean, what if...

47:07.934 --> 47:10.358
...what if meeting him makes me remember?

47:11.734 --> 47:13.938
If I could just remember what
happened the night we crashed...

47:14.018 --> 47:16.608
...maybe we could use that to get help...

47:16.734 --> 47:18.825
...to get rid of this thing.

47:21.068 --> 47:22.621
That's...

47:23.000 --> 47:24.892
...it's a lot of ifs.

47:28.568 --> 47:30.426
No, you should do it.

47:31.135 --> 47:32.958
You should go.

47:33.634 --> 47:35.688
What do you mean, I should go?

47:36.601 --> 47:38.015
I'm staying here.

47:39.201 --> 47:41.212
- What?
- It's too dangerous out there.

47:41.292 --> 47:42.971
- I'm a ticking time bomb.
- Liam...

47:43.051 --> 47:44.821
Do you know how many people
could've died back there?

47:44.901 --> 47:46.595
Yeah, but they didn't.

47:46.674 --> 47:48.887
It was luck. That's all.

47:48.967 --> 47:51.092
I don't believe this.
You think it's gonna be safer here?

47:51.172 --> 47:52.958
How long before you think somebody
comes snooping around?

47:53.038 --> 47:58.121
- I'll wait in the woods until you come back.
- Jesus Christ, I'm not going alone!

47:58.501 --> 48:02.556
What if this guy isn't even who he says he is?
What if he's the reason I went missing?

48:03.335 --> 48:06.425
I could be running away
from him for all we know.

48:09.100 --> 48:10.658
Liam?

48:12.900 --> 48:14.758
I need you.

48:46.068 --> 48:50.121
All right, there are three of them in
Smithburg, but look at this one at the bottom.

48:50.201 --> 48:51.388
Daerwood Press.

48:51.468 --> 48:54.687
See, I think I remember them saying
something on the radio that he had a store.

48:54.767 --> 48:57.459
- All right. Let's get the hell out of here.
- [CAR STARTS]

49:15.968 --> 49:17.388
Sam Daerwood?

49:17.967 --> 49:21.821
Rose? Oh, my God!
Where have you been? Are you okay?

49:21.901 --> 49:24.943
- I'm fine. Just get in the car.
- What?

49:25.023 --> 49:28.139
Please, I can't get into this
right now. Just get in the car.

49:29.401 --> 49:31.406
Holy shit.

49:32.201 --> 49:36.046
- Rose, tell me everything's all right.
- I'm fine. Just get in the car.

49:37.600 --> 49:42.080
- Fuck this. Rose, get out...
- Sam! Do you trust me?

49:42.160 --> 49:45.158
- Rose, what are...
- If you trust me, you will get in the car.

49:57.667 --> 49:59.955
What the hell is going on?
Where are we going?

50:00.035 --> 50:02.092
We need your help.

50:07.368 --> 50:10.408
- This is insane.
- Sam.

50:10.867 --> 50:13.892
SAM: And you honestly expect me
to believe all of this?

50:15.500 --> 50:19.155
Clearly this guy is a terrorist or a goddamn
psycho and he's got you brainwashed.

50:19.235 --> 50:21.684
- You're not listening to me.
- Rose, I don't believe for a second...

50:21.764 --> 50:24.055
...that you don't remember who I am.

50:24.634 --> 50:26.491
I don't.

50:26.884 --> 50:29.492
No. No way.

50:31.000 --> 50:34.625
And this crazy bullshit, I mean,
who the fuck are you anyway?

50:37.301 --> 50:39.155
- What are you doing?
- I am ending this now.

50:39.235 --> 50:42.454
- Sam, please give me the phone.
- I am calling the police and we are leaving.

50:42.534 --> 50:44.148
I can't do that.

50:44.567 --> 50:47.592
So if you won't help us,
I am gonna have to go.

50:49.440 --> 50:51.492
- Rose...
- LIAM: Hey!

50:59.135 --> 51:00.855
- Step back.
- What?

51:00.935 --> 51:02.792
Just do it.

51:09.667 --> 51:13.111
- Holy shit.
- Stop. Stop. It's okay.

51:15.500 --> 51:16.958
Sam.

51:17.594 --> 51:19.437
Can we trust you?

51:34.500 --> 51:36.391
You guys can hide out back here.

51:39.900 --> 51:42.420
SAM: It's not much, but it's out of the way.

51:43.080 --> 51:45.315
I can keep the shop closed
for a couple of days, but...

51:45.394 --> 51:48.084
...after that, I mean...
what's the plan here?

51:48.164 --> 51:51.115
I... I mean, we're still trying to figure
that out. We have to get in touch...

51:51.195 --> 51:53.487
...with, like, a researcher or scientist.

51:53.567 --> 51:56.121
- So we'll need your help.
- Okay.

51:56.201 --> 51:58.624
And maybe have you act
as, like, a middle man.

51:58.704 --> 52:01.288
But I don't... I don't know.

52:01.367 --> 52:03.570
Yeah, I'll see what I can do.

52:03.650 --> 52:06.255
We should wait until everything
in the media dies down.

52:06.335 --> 52:08.255
- JANE: Oh, he's right.
- Right.

52:08.335 --> 52:12.055
First things first, we gotta
get rid of that car out there.

52:12.135 --> 52:14.216
A buddy of mine owns a scrap yard.
I can take it there.

52:14.296 --> 52:15.855
Are you sure?

52:15.935 --> 52:18.976
He's a friend of ours.
We've known him for years.

52:22.168 --> 52:23.992
All right.

52:25.135 --> 52:26.958
I'll be right back.

52:31.968 --> 52:33.655
He seems like a good guy.

52:37.534 --> 52:40.554
WOMAN ON TV: <i>...as to why an upstanding
Smithburg citizen like Daerwood...</i>

52:40.634 --> 52:42.820
<i>...would seemingly go along
for the ride with Hartwell...</i>

52:42.900 --> 52:45.320
<i>...a man who is considered
both armed and dangerous.</i>

52:45.400 --> 52:47.888
<i>To make matters worse,
an eye witness at the hospital...</i>

52:47.968 --> 52:51.320
<i>...reports seeing Hartwell and Daerwood
in each other's arms at one point...</i>

52:51.400 --> 52:54.521
<i>...which begs the question, is Rose
Daerwood in some sort of relationship...</i>

52:54.601 --> 52:57.921
<i>...with this man, and if so,
to what degree is she helping him?</i>

52:58.001 --> 53:01.042
- <i>Can she be considered an accomplice?</i>
- Jesus!

53:01.122 --> 53:03.191
[TV TURNS OFF]

53:05.300 --> 53:07.542
JANE: I wonder what's taking him so long.

53:15.135 --> 53:16.692
What is it?

53:17.334 --> 53:20.258
- It's you.
- What the hell?

53:21.400 --> 53:22.855
Lily Grayson?

53:22.935 --> 53:25.017
It says you've been missing for over a year.

53:27.350 --> 53:30.775
SAM: Rose? What's going on?

53:41.467 --> 53:44.758
SAM: Even though you were the same age,
you always called her your big sister.

53:48.767 --> 53:50.358
What happened to her?

53:52.600 --> 53:54.692
Look, can we do this in private?

53:56.000 --> 53:57.854
It's all right.

53:58.034 --> 53:59.725
I'll wait here.

54:03.800 --> 54:06.629
SAM: The police said she left work
one night and just...

54:07.468 --> 54:09.357
...never came home.

54:12.400 --> 54:14.257
She's still missing.

54:16.020 --> 54:18.354
Look, let's not do this now,
not with everything that's going on.

54:18.434 --> 54:20.720
- Why not?
- Later.

54:20.800 --> 54:24.224
Sam, anything can help, please.

54:27.467 --> 54:30.092
Look, after the police
didn't find any leads...

54:31.500 --> 54:33.320
...you took it pretty hard.

54:33.800 --> 54:37.996
You started putting posters up
all over town, started missing work.

54:39.199 --> 54:41.025
You got really depressed.

54:42.324 --> 54:45.058
It was a rough patch on us.
We fought all the time.

54:46.100 --> 54:49.284
- And last week was just hell.
- What do you mean?

54:50.434 --> 54:53.287
It had been one year
since Lily disappeared and...

54:54.067 --> 54:57.557
...you showed up here and started
making photocopies for a poster.

54:57.637 --> 54:59.892
It was like it was starting all over again.

55:02.484 --> 55:05.142
We had this huge fight and you stormed off.

55:06.467 --> 55:09.887
I didn't make a big deal of it at first because
we've had this kind of fight before and...

55:09.967 --> 55:12.310
...you always come back after a few days.

55:12.750 --> 55:15.948
You usually stay in a motel or something.

55:16.934 --> 55:18.572
At least that's what you tell me.

55:36.700 --> 55:38.757
[SNIFFLING]

55:43.467 --> 55:45.918
You know there's better ways to die.

55:47.067 --> 55:49.092
Shit. Just...

55:51.267 --> 55:54.009
- ...just fucking get out of here.
- What's your name?

55:54.089 --> 55:55.924
Just go!

55:56.900 --> 55:58.577
If that's what you want.

56:00.634 --> 56:03.487
Better make sure you dive in
head first, though...

56:04.067 --> 56:05.675
...because from this height...

56:06.934 --> 56:09.758
...best case scenario,
you'll probably break your neck...

56:11.500 --> 56:13.725
...and the rest of your life in a wheelchair.

56:16.334 --> 56:18.575
I just miss her so much.

56:27.534 --> 56:29.424
LIAM: Come on.

56:41.167 --> 56:43.224
Can I drive you home?

56:44.834 --> 56:46.357
No.

56:52.035 --> 56:53.921
It's too late for that.

56:54.400 --> 56:56.858
You don't have to explain yourself to me.

56:59.700 --> 57:01.992
Look, we can go anywhere you want.

57:04.834 --> 57:06.658
You can't stay here.

57:45.717 --> 57:47.862
Just drive.

57:49.834 --> 57:51.768
My name is Liam.

57:53.800 --> 57:55.557
I'm Rose.

57:55.640 --> 57:58.187
- Rose?
- Yes, I'm okay.

57:58.267 --> 58:00.420
- What is it?
- It's nothing.

58:00.500 --> 58:03.991
- You can talk to me.
- I... I'm okay.

58:07.467 --> 58:10.758
You wouldn't happen to have
any food around here, would you?

58:11.267 --> 58:12.738
Uh, no.

58:13.900 --> 58:17.720
But maybe I can swing by the house
and pick up some stuff.

58:17.800 --> 58:21.371
That... that would be great. Thank you.

58:26.997 --> 58:29.054
REPORTER: <i>Authorities speculate
that Hartwell and Daerwood...</i>

58:29.134 --> 58:31.554
<i>...may be taking refuge
somewhere in the tri-county area.</i>

58:31.634 --> 58:33.491
Where's Sam?

58:34.900 --> 58:36.820
What's the matter?

58:36.900 --> 58:41.717
That night at the bridge, you and me,
we didn't know each other, not before that.

58:42.986 --> 58:44.832
You don't understand.

58:46.767 --> 58:48.858
You saved my life.

59:02.034 --> 59:05.197
Jane? Jane, get up.

59:05.900 --> 59:08.237
JANE: Hey. You're back.

59:08.317 --> 59:10.054
Yeah.

59:10.134 --> 59:11.775
Brought you some things.

59:11.855 --> 59:14.692
Oh, my God. Thank you so much.

59:15.567 --> 59:17.788
SAM: I brought some sleeping bags.

59:18.634 --> 59:20.457
They're by the door.

